Package metrics

Class SimulatorHistogram

java.lang.Object
metrics.SimulatorMetric
metrics.SimulatorHistogram
All Implemented Interfaces:
HistogramCollector
public class SimulatorHistogram extends SimulatorMetric implements HistogramCollector
This class provides a prometheus-based histogram for extracting metrics. For every registered metric, the metric will be collected for each node separately

    • startTimer

      public boolean startTimer​(String name, UUID id, String timerId)
      Starts time for recording duration and adds it to histogram with a specific name, and timer ID. The time recording finishes when observeDuration is called with the same name, and timer ID. The time elapsed will be recorded under the node with the given id. If two timers start with the same timer ID, the observeDuration will stop the earliest one.
      Specified by:
      startTimer in interface HistogramCollector
      Parameters:
      name - name of the metric.
      id - id of the node.
      timerId - id of the timer.
      Returns:
      false if metric is null else return true

    • observeDuration

      public boolean observeDuration​(String name, String timerId)
      Observe the duration of the already started timer with a specific name and timer ID. To start a timer, please use the startTimer method.
      Specified by:
      observeDuration in interface HistogramCollector
      Parameters:
      name - name of the timer
      timerId - id of the timer
      Returns:
      false if there is an exception else return true.

    • tryObserveDuration

      public void tryObserveDuration​(String name, String timerId)
      Silently observes the duration of the already started timer with a specific name and timer ID. In case timer has not already been started, it simply returns without logging any error.
      Specified by:
      tryObserveDuration in interface HistogramCollector
      Parameters:
      name - name of the timer
      timerId - id of the timer
